link: Antti Karttunen, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..65537
Index entries for sequences computed from indices in prime factorization
program: A241909(n) = if(1==n||isprime(n),2^primepi(n),my(f=factor(n),h=1,i,m=1,p=1,k=1); while(k<=#f~, p = nextprime(1+p); i = primepi(f[k,1]); m *= p^(i-h); h = i; if(f[k,2]>1, f[k,2]--, k++)); (p*m));
